  "local_port": 38508,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some popular drink/shots to get at the bar?",
  "response": "Here are some popular drinks and shots you might consider ordering at the bar:\n\n### Classic Cocktails\n1. **Margarita** - Typically made with tequila, lime juice, and orange liqueur, served with salt on the rim.\n2. **Old Fashioned** - A classic whiskey cocktail made with bourbon or rye, sugar, bitters, and a twist of citrus.\n3. **Martini** - A mix of gin and dry vermouth, garnished with an olive or a lemon twist; you can also order it with vodka.\n4. **Mojito** - A refreshing cocktail made with rum, mint, lime juice, sugar, and soda water.\n5. **Cosmopolitan** - A mix of vodka, triple sec, cranberry juice, and lime juice, often served in a martini glass.\n\n### Shots\n1. **Tequila Shot** - Typically served with salt and lime; popular for celebratory occasions.\n2. **J\u00e4gerbomb** - A mix of J\u00e4germeister and energy drink; dropped into a glass and consumed quickly.\n3. **Lemon Drop** - A sweet and tart vodka shot with lemon juice and simple syrup, often served with a sugar rim.\n4. **Fireball Cinnamon Whisky Shot** - Known for its sweet and spicy flavor, it's a favorite among many.\n5. **B-52** - A layered shot made with Kahl\u00faa, Baileys Irish Cream, and Grand Marnier.\n\n### Modern Favorites\n1. **Espresso Martini** - A caffeinated twist on the classic martini, made with vodka, espresso, coffee liqueur, and sugar syrup.\n2. **Pina Colada** - A tropical blend of rum, coconut cream, and pineapple juice, often garnished with a cherry.\n3. **Aperol Spritz** - A refreshing drink made with Aperol, Prosecco, and soda water, garnished with an orange slice.\n4. **Sangria** - A fruity wine punch, traditional in Spanish cultures, typically made with red or white wine, fruit, and a splash of brandy or soda.\n\n### Non-Alcoholic Options\n1. **Shirley Temple** - A mix of ginger ale and grenadine, garnished with a maraschino cherry.\n2. **Virgin Mojito** - Lime juice, mint, and soda water for a refreshing, non-alcoholic version of the mojito.\n3. **Arnold Palmer** - A blend of iced tea and lemonade.\n\nWhen you're at the bar, don't hesitate to ask the bartender for their favorites or any house specials!",
